  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to explore the changes in metabolic parameters in patients
      treated with escitalopram for six months for major depression, generalized anxiety disorder
      or panic disorder, with or without agoraphobia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      This is an open-label study, with 4 scheduled visits. Recruitment of 100 subjects.
      Assessments include demographics, diagnosis, smoking frequency, Clinical Global Scale
      (CGI-S), weight, height,blood pressure, waist and hip circumference and fasting blood glucose
      and lipd profile.

      Statistical analysis will be exploratory and mainly descriptive.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
